sitar an interactive text processing system for small computers sitar a lowcost in teractive text handling and text analysis system for nontechnical users  is in many ways comparable to in teractive bibliographical search and retrieval systems but has several  additional features it is implemented on a pdp11 timesharing computer invoked by a crt with microprogrammed  editing functions  it uses a simple command language designating a function a file and a search template  consisting of the textual string desired and strings delimiting the context in which the hit is to be  delivered  extensive experience with sitar shows that the combined powers of simple commands string  orientation circular file structure a crt with local memory and conversational computing produce a  system much more powerful than the sum of its parts cacm july 1977 schneider b r jr watts r m 